In this article, President Biden speaks to a group of mayors at the White House, thanking them for their leadership and discussing various topics, including the impact of mayors on their communities, the progress made in his first two years as President, the importance of investing in America and rebuilding the economy, the need for mental health support, and the role of mayors in addressing issues such as public safety, infrastructure, and climate change. He also emphasizes the need for unity in the country and the importance of working together to solve problems.